<br>
Last night I went on a Hate run, and it was the guilds first time since the changes to Hate, so I did not even bother with the pet point. But things I learned...<br>
<br>
A level 53 Mage is almost completely ineffective against the new mobs on the upper floors in terms of casting, the failure rate was 90% when it was not malo'd and 50% when it was Malo'd. I tried all the tools available and had varying success.<br>
<br>
Shock of Swords: 1 in 32 stuck for full<br>
Elemental Maelstorm: Never stuck except with Malo<br>
Char: Best success but still nothing to write home to Jababer about<br>
Lava Bolt: Cannot remember for sure but I had one stick in several hours and the mob summoned and killed me.<br>
<br>
FYI my best luck was vs Knights of Innoruuk.<br>
<br>
The only time I summoned a pet the entire night was once when we ended up with like 7 mobs. I summoned a pet and so did the others ( I would like to think off of my lead :-) heh we had 6 mages there and I saw 5 pets as I camped out) I did not summon it until the order to camp out came, then I did so and sent it at the mob that was caster hunting (used the 51 Voc: earth) threw a BO at it and camped. I did have 2 people mention in tells that without the pet they would have died and added to the CR. <br>
<br>
But one thing seems apparent, the new mobs are not that pullable(hmm is that a word) it is best to move to them, then spend a while in each spot then move on, it is possible that on the upper floors, guilds may begin to change their thoughts on the issue, the mobs cannot really be mezzed, so extra tanks make sense.<br>
<br>
I would propose that talk with your guild and suggest that you have a pet group once you leave the first floor and that they are assigned adds as they come. This stops the splitting up of PC tanks and saves cleric mana ( not to mention gets mages and necros some well deserved exp :-)<br>
<br>
BTW the Maestro room does have pathing so bad, that it is the only place that I prefer myself not to use a pet, you can send it at a mob ten feet away and it will zig zag 10 minutes getting to it. <br>
<br>
Oh yeah and the AC22 16INT 10PR and DR Robe looks so good I will be dropping my pally pic soon :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzurrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zurrin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(3/20/01 7:36:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My thoughts</span><hr size=1> No rules about pets in my guild except if you can't control them don't summon them.<br>
