<br>
Did you know that when Hate first opened, all the revenants had pets? And all the golems had pets? But the pathing in Hate is so bad that the pets were getting stuck everywhere, and causing major lag and trains.<br>
<br>
(plus back then mobs could have tons of pets....anyone remember the pet stacks in lake rathe?)<br>
<br>
Soo....instead of fixing the pathing...they removed mob pets. But player pets still get stuck places and generally pathe horribly.<br>
<br>
Therefore pretty early on it was established that one shouldn't have a pet up in Hate...and this tradition still lives on.<br>
<br>
Besides...when you already have 40+ people there, you really dont *need* to have a pet up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usildaardm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SildaarDM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(3/20/01 10:11:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My thoughts</span><hr size=1> Well my thoughts are, keep an open mind and don't exclude viable options. Yes, many times pets are not a good idea. Pathing is really bad. <br>
<br>
I did Hate last night with my guild and we did a portal breakin. The breakin got a little hairy and the order was given to break out the pets. The mobs were beaten down in no time and life went on. When we moved, the pets died. When it was safe to use pets again, the order was given. Fortunately we had some great raid leaders who understood the value of pets, and their weaknesses. I was a bit concerned when pets were used against Maestro. I kept seeing about 8 pets being fluxed to the ceiling. I was afraid that they would agro the second floor but that didn't happen.<br>
<br>
I understand your frustration, my first Hate raid pets were not allowed, and I felt like a second rate wizard. But you might want to ask that question before you sign up for a raid if you feel that strongly. Personally I go for the fun...and if no pets are allowed then the raid leader better realize that they've just cut my right arm off. <p><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.owid.com/Sild-sig6.JPG" width="500" height="75">

